description:
&lt;p&gt;An enthusiastic support worker is required to join the adult Speech and Language Therapy Service based at Liskeard Community Hospital. This post offers the opportunity to work on wards, clinics and in the community and is suitable for a person who has health care experience working with people who have communication problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will work under the guidance of qualified Speech and language therapists but without direct supervision . They will be expected to see a variety of adult patients and undertake some basic administrative support. Whilst the post is based at Liskeard Community Hospital, the post-holder will be expected to work anywhere within the N&amp;E team area and may be required to provide input to sites in Bodmin and Launceston.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The support worker will be a member of the East Team and will participate in team meetings, training and supervision. Support is available from experienced specialists and on site staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is for 22.5 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKathy GreensidesAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kathy Greensides 01579373590&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
